Accordion
---------------
It is a series of panels stacked on the top of each other.

Accordion menus are widely used in web applications to manage huge amount of data and navigation lists in small amount
of area.



<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Accordion</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
        integrity="sha384-YvpcrYf0tY3lHB60NNkmXc5s9fDVZLESaAA55NDzOxhy9GkcIdslK1eN7N6jIeHz"
        crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="accordion" id="firstaccordion">
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h3 class="accordion-header" id="headingthree">
                    <button type="button" class="accordion-button collapsed" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#collapsethree">
                        HTML
                    </button>
                </h3>
                <div id="collapsethree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="firstaccordion">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p>
                            HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the most basic building block of the Web. It defines the
                            meaning and structure of web content. Other technologies besides HTML are generally used to
                            describe a web page's appearance/presentation (CSS) or functionality/behavior (JavaScript).
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h3 class="accordion-header" id="headingthree">
                    <button type="button" class="accordion-button collapsed" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                        data-bs-target="#collapsethree1">
                        HTML
                    </button>
                </h3>
                <div id="collapsethree1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="firstaccordion">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p>
                            HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the most basic building block of the Web. It defines the
                            meaning and structure of web content. Other technologies besides HTML are generally used to
                            describe a web page's appearance/presentation (CSS) or functionality/behavior (JavaScript).
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>

